	"readme": "# svelte-keycon  [![npm version](https://badge.fury.io/js/vue-svelte.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/js/svelte-keycon) \n\nSvelte Keyboard Controller\n\n## Installation\n```\nnpm i svelte-keycon\n```\n\n## How to use\n```svelte\n<script>\nimport { ref } from \"@cfcs/svelte\";\nimport { useKeycon } from \"svlete-keycon\";\n\n\nconst containerRef = ref();\nconst {\n  isKeydown,\n  onBlur,\n  onKeydown,\n  onKeyup,\n} = useKeycon({\n  // If you want to specify a specific input, use ref. If not used, the event is used for the window.\n  ref: containerRef,\n  keys: [\"shift\"],\n});\n\nonKeydown(() => {\n  console.log(\"keydown\");\n});\n\nonKeyup(() => {\n  console.log(\"keyup\");\n});\n\nonBlur(() => {\n  console.log(\"blur\");\n});\n</script>\n<div use:containerRef>{ $isKeydown ? \"keydown\" : \"keyup\" }</div>\n```",
